abstract: The risk of a disorderly Brexit will remain even after Britain leaves the European Union (EU) this week, Germany's powerful BDI industry association said on Tuesday, urging both sides to aim for a basic trade agreement by the end of the year.
snippet: The risk of a disorderly Brexit will remain even after Britain leaves the European Union (EU) this week, Germany's powerful BDI industry association said on Tuesday, urging both sides to aim for a basic trade agreement by the end of the year.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — The risk of a disorderly Brexit will remain even after Britain leaves the European Union (EU) this week, Germany's powerful BDI industry association said on Tuesday, urging both sides to aim for a basic trade agreement by the end of the year.
headline_main: German Industry Bloc Says Hard Brexit Risk Remains
headline_print_headline: German Industry Bloc Says Hard Brexit Risk Remains

abstract: New Hampshire isn't used to being neglected.

abstract: The British royal said he would help American officials investigating  possible sex trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein’s associates, but so far he has ignored their requests.
snippet: The British royal said he would help American officials investigating  possible sex trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein’s associates, but so far he has ignored their requests.
lead_paragraph: Two months ago, Britain’s Prince Andrew issued a public statement saying he would be willing to help American law enforcement officials with their investigation into allegations of sex-trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein and his associates.

abstract: Candidates running for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination have been uniformly critical of the immigration policies of U.S. President Donald Trump, who was elected after promising to crack down on illegal immigration and bolster enforcement along the U.S.-Mexico border.
snippet: Candidates running for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination have been uniformly critical of the immigration policies of U.S. President Donald Trump, who was elected after promising to crack down on illegal immigration and bolster enforcemen...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Candidates running for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination have been uniformly critical of the immigration policies of U.S. President Donald Trump, who was elected after promising to crack down on illegal immigration and bolster enforcement along the U.S.-Mexico border.
headline_main: Democratic U.S. Presidential Hopefuls Seek Contrast With Trump on Immigration
headline_print_headline: Democratic U.S. Presidential Hopefuls Seek Contrast With Trump on Immigration

abstract: Health officials in the United States said more than 100 people were being evaluated for possible infection. Of the nearly 3,000 people who have contracted the virus, the vast majority live in China.

abstract: At nearly nine p.m. on Saturday, Samy Amkieh was about to head back to his office after braving 20 degree temperatures to knock on doors for three hours in East Des Moines. But the 20-year-old field organizer knocked on one more door and was rewarded by convincing the resident to be a team leader for Bernie Sanders at a nearby caucus location.
snippet: At nearly nine p.m. on Saturday, Samy Amkieh was about to head back to his office after braving 20 degree temperatures to knock on doors for three hours in East Des Moines. But the 20-year-old field organizer knocked on one more door and was rewar...
lead_paragraph: ANKENY, Iowa — At nearly nine p.m. on Saturday, Samy Amkieh was about to head back to his office after braving 20 degree temperatures to knock on doors for three hours in East Des Moines. But the 20-year-old field organizer knocked on one more door and was rewarded by convincing the resident to be a team leader for Bernie Sanders at a nearby caucus location.
headline_main: Organization Becomes Critical in Final Week Before Iowa Vote

abstract: Ruben Diaz Jr., the Bronx borough president, said that he would no longer seek public office and hoped to spend more time with his family.
snippet: Ruben Diaz Jr., the Bronx borough president, said that he would no longer seek public office and hoped to spend more time with his family.
lead_paragraph: For nearly his entire adult life, Ruben Diaz Jr. had seemed to be on a one-way path to political stardom.

abstract: “It makes you realize that you’ve got to make every day count,” the former vice president said.
snippet: “It makes you realize that you’ve got to make every day count,” the former vice president said.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — At former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s second campaign stop of the day, an event hosted by the Des Moines branch of the N.A.A.C.P. and two local organizations, Creative Visions and Urban Dreams, the audience was informed that the basketball superstar Kobe Bryant had been killed in a helicopter crash, along with four other people, and a moment of silence was observed.
headline_main: At Biden event, a moment of silence for Kobe Bryant.

abstract: With four strong polls on Saturday and Sunday, Mr. Yang, who missed the last debate, has secured a spot onstage in New Hampshire on Feb. 7.
snippet: With four strong polls on Saturday and Sunday, Mr. Yang, who missed the last debate, has secured a spot onstage in New Hampshire on Feb. 7.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The entrepreneur Andrew Yang qualified for the next Democratic debate with a string of four strong polls released in quick succession on Saturday and Sunday.
